  32:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   @verbatim
  33:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   ==============================================================================
  34:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****                       ##### TIMER Generic features #####
  35:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   ==============================================================================
  36:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   [..] The Timer features include:
  37:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****        (#) 16-bit up, down, up/down auto-reload counter.
  38:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****        (#) 16-bit programmable prescaler allowing dividing (also on the fly) the
  39:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****            counter clock frequency either by any factor between 1 and 65536.
  40:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****        (#) Up to 4 independent channels for:
  41:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****            (++) Input Capture
  42:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****            (++) Output Compare
  43:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****            (++) PWM generation (Edge and Center-aligned Mode)
  44:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****            (++) One-pulse mode output
  45:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****        (#) Synchronization circuit to control the timer with external signals and to interconnect
  46:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****             several timers together.
  47:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****        (#) Supports incremental encoder for positioning purposes
  48:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c **** 
  49:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****             ##### How to use this driver #####
  50:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   ==============================================================================
  51:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     [..]
  52:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****      (#) Initialize the TIM low level resources by implementing the following functions
  53:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****          depending on the selected feature:
  54:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****            (++) Time Base : HAL_TIM_Base_MspInit()
  55:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****            (++) Input Capture : HAL_TIM_IC_MspInit()
  56:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****            (++) Output Compare : HAL_TIM_OC_MspInit()
  57:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****            (++) PWM generation : HAL_TIM_PWM_MspInit()
  58:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****            (++) One-pulse mode output : HAL_TIM_OnePulse_MspInit()
  59:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****            (++) Encoder mode output : HAL_TIM_Encoder_MspInit()
  60:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c **** 
  61:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****      (#) Initialize the TIM low level resources :
  62:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****         (##) Enable the TIM interface clock using __HAL_RCC_TIMx_CLK_ENABLE();
  63:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****         (##) TIM pins configuration
  64:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****             (+++) Enable the clock for the TIM GPIOs using the following function:
  65:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****              __HAL_RCC_GPIOx_CLK_ENABLE();
  66:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****             (+++) Configure these TIM pins in Alternate function mode using HAL_GPIO_Init();
  67:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c **** 
  68:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****      (#) The external Clock can be configured, if needed (the default clock is the
  69:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****          internal clock from the APBx), using the following function:
  70:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****          HAL_TIM_ConfigClockSource, the clock configuration should be done before
  71:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****          any start function.
  72:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c **** 
  73:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****      (#) Configure the TIM in the desired functioning mode using one of the
  74:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****        Initialization function of this driver:
  75:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****        (++) HAL_TIM_Base_Init: to use the Timer to generate a simple time base
  76:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****        (++) HAL_TIM_OC_Init and HAL_TIM_OC_ConfigChannel: to use the Timer to generate an
  77:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****             Output Compare signal.
  78:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****        (++) HAL_TIM_PWM_Init and HAL_TIM_PWM_ConfigChannel: to use the Timer to generate a
  79:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****             PWM signal.
  80:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****        (++) HAL_TIM_IC_Init and HAL_TIM_IC_ConfigChannel: to use the Timer to measure an
  81:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****             external signal.
  82:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****        (++) HAL_TIM_OnePulse_Init and HAL_TIM_OnePulse_ConfigChannel: to use the Timer
  83:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****             in One Pulse Mode.
  84:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****        (++) HAL_TIM_Encoder_Init: to use the Timer Encoder Interface.
  85:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c **** 
  86:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****      (#) Activate the TIM peripheral using one of the start functions depending from the feature us
  87:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****            (++) Time Base : HAL_TIM_Base_Start(), HAL_TIM_Base_Start_DMA(), HAL_TIM_Base_Start_IT()
ARM GAS  C:\Users\LENOVO\AppData\Local\Temp\ccxLuvMR.s 			page 3


  88:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****            (++) Input Capture :  HAL_TIM_IC_Start(), HAL_TIM_IC_Start_DMA(), HAL_TIM_IC_Start_IT()
  89:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****            (++) Output Compare : HAL_TIM_OC_Start(), HAL_TIM_OC_Start_DMA(), HAL_TIM_OC_Start_IT()
  90:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****            (++) PWM generation : HAL_TIM_PWM_Start(), HAL_TIM_PWM_Start_DMA(), HAL_TIM_PWM_Start_IT
  91:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****            (++) One-pulse mode output : HAL_TIM_OnePulse_Start(), HAL_TIM_OnePulse_Start_IT()
  92:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****            (++) Encoder mode output : HAL_TIM_Encoder_Start(), HAL_TIM_Encoder_Start_DMA(), HAL_TIM
  93:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c **** 
  94:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****      (#) The DMA Burst is managed with the two following functions:
  95:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****          HAL_TIM_DMABurst_WriteStart()
  96:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****          HAL_TIM_DMABurst_ReadStart()
  97:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c **** 
  98:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     *** Callback registration ***
  99:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   =============================================
 100:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c **** 
 101:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   [..]
 102:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   The compilation define  USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
 103:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
 104:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c **** 
 105:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   [..]
 106:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   Use Function @ref HAL_TIM_RegisterCallback() to register a callback.
 107:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   @ref HAL_TIM_RegisterCallback() takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 108:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   the Callback ID and a pointer to the user callback function.
 109:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c **** 
 110:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   [..]
 111:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   Use function @ref HAL_TIM_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
 112:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   weak function.
 113:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   @ref HAL_TIM_UnRegisterCallback takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 114:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   and the Callback ID.
 115:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c **** 
 116:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   [..]
 117:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   These functions allow to register/unregister following callbacks:
 118:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) Base_MspInitCallback              : TIM Base Msp Init Callback.
 119:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) Base_MspDeInitCallback            : TIM Base Msp DeInit Callback.
 120:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) IC_MspInitCallback                : TIM IC Msp Init Callback.
 121:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) IC_MspDeInitCallback              : TIM IC Msp DeInit Callback.
 122:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) OC_MspInitCallback                : TIM OC Msp Init Callback.
 123:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) OC_MspDeInitCallback              : TIM OC Msp DeInit Callback.
 124:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) PWM_MspInitCallback               : TIM PWM Msp Init Callback.
 125:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) PWM_MspDeInitCallback             : TIM PWM Msp DeInit Callback.
 126:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) OnePulse_MspInitCallback          : TIM One Pulse Msp Init Callback.
 127:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) OnePulse_MspDeInitCallback        : TIM One Pulse Msp DeInit Callback.
 128:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) Encoder_MspInitCallback           : TIM Encoder Msp Init Callback.
 129:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) Encoder_MspDeInitCallback         : TIM Encoder Msp DeInit Callback.
 130:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) HallSensor_MspInitCallback        : TIM Hall Sensor Msp Init Callback.
 131:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) HallSensor_MspDeInitCallback      : TIM Hall Sensor Msp DeInit Callback.
 132:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) PeriodElapsedCallback             : TIM Period Elapsed Callback.
 133:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) PeriodElapsedHalfCpltCallback     : TIM Period Elapsed half complete Callback.
 134:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) TriggerCallback                   : TIM Trigger Callback.
 135:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) TriggerHalfCpltCallback           : TIM Trigger half complete Callback.
 136:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) IC_CaptureCallback                : TIM Input Capture Callback.
 137:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) IC_CaptureHalfCpltCallback        : TIM Input Capture half complete Callback.
 138:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) OC_DelayElapsedCallback           : TIM Output Compare Delay Elapsed Callback.
 139:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) PWM_PulseFinishedCallback         : TIM PWM Pulse Finished Callback.
 140:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) PWM_PulseFinishedHalfCpltCallback : TIM PWM Pulse Finished half complete Callback.
 141:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback                     : TIM Error Callback.
 142:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) CommutationCallback               : TIM Commutation Callback.
 143:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) CommutationHalfCpltCallback       : TIM Commutation half complete Callback.
 144:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     (+) BreakCallback                     : TIM Break Callback.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\LENOVO\AppData\Local\Temp\ccxLuvMR.s 			page 4


 145:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c **** 
 146:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   [..]
 147:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c **** By default, after the Init and when the state is HAL_TIM_STATE_RESET
 148:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c **** all interrupt callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
 149:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   examples @ref HAL_TIM_TriggerCallback(), @ref HAL_TIM_ErrorCallback().
 150:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c **** 
 151:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   [..]
 152:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are reset to the legacy weak
 153:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   functionalities in the Init / DeInit only when these callbacks are null
 154:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   (not registered beforehand). If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the Init / DeInit
 155:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     keep and use the user MspInit / MspDeInit callbacks(registered beforehand)
 156:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c **** 
 157:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   [..]
 158:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     Callbacks can be registered / unregistered in HAL_TIM_STATE_READY state only.
 159:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     Exception done MspInit / MspDeInit that can be registered / unregistered
 160:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     in HAL_TIM_STATE_READY or HAL_TIM_STATE_RESET state,
 161:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****     thus registered(user) MspInit / DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init / DeInit.
 162:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****   In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 163:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c ****       using @ref HAL_TIM_RegisterCallback() before calling DeInit or Init function.
 164:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_tim.c **** 
